Moonraker / Klipper 3D Printer Driver for Hubitat
Author: jdthomas24  ·  Version: 1.0.0  ·  License: Apache 2.0
Integrates any Moonraker/Klipper 3D printer with Hubitat. Monitor status, temps, and progress via a live dashboard tile. Start, pause, resume, and cancel prints from Hubitat or any automation rule.

Requirements

Hubitat Elevation hub
Printer running Klipper + Moonraker
Hub must reach the printer IP on the Moonraker port (default 7125) over your local network


Installation

In Hubitat go to Drivers Code → New Driver, paste the driver code, and click Save
Go to Devices → Add Device → Virtual
Name the device to match your printer (e.g. 3D - CR10 Pro 1) — do this before saving preferences
Set Type to Moonraker Klipper Printer and click Save Device
Fill in preferences and click Save Preferences

Repeat for each printer.

Setup
Sonicpad
All printers share one IP — use the port to differentiate. Create one Hubitat device per printer:
USB PortMoonraker PortPort 17125Port 27126Port 37127Port 47128
Unoccupied ports will show offline — this is normal.
Standard Install (Raspberry Pi, BTT Pi, etc.)
Each printer has its own IP, all using port 7125.
Preferences
SettingNotesPrinter IP AddressSonicpad: all printers share the same IPMoonraker PortDefault 7125 — see table above for SonicpadUse HTTPSLeave off for most local installsAPI KeyOnly needed if Moonraker enforces auth. Find it at http://<ip>:<port>/access/api_keyPoll Interval10–30 seconds recommended while printingRecent Files LimitTop 20 recommendedTemperature UnitCelsius (default) or Fahrenheit

Dashboard Tiles
Add either tile to your Hubitat dashboard as an Attribute tile.
aaStatusTile — full printer dashboard showing online status, klipper state, print state, current filename, hotend and bed temps vs target, progress bar, elapsed/remaining time, ETA, fan speed, and filament status.
filesListTile — recent prints browser showing top 20 files sorted by print history. Currently printing file is pinned green at #1. Last completed print shown at top. Use the file number with the startPrint command.

Troubleshooting
"klipper: unknown" in tile — hit Initialize on the device. Fixes on next poll.
Temps showing in wrong unit — go to preferences, switch Temperature Unit to Celsius, hit Save Preferences. One-time fix per device.
"0 prints done" in tile — hit Refresh File List to load print history.
Printer shows offline but is running — hit Refresh or Initialize to force reconnect.
startPrint fails — verify the printer is on and Moonraker is running. Check IP and port in preferences.
File list numbers look wrong — hit Refresh File List to rebuild from current print history.
